datastructures.trees

Class LinkedBinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.trees.LinkedBinarySearchTree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BinarySearchTree<T>, Tree<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AVLBinarySearchTree, RedBlackBinarySearchTree

    public class LinkedBinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements BinarySearchTree<T>
    LinkedBinarySearchTree is an implementation of a BinarySearchTree using links. It is by far the most commonly encountered binary tree implementation. Compared to an array-based implementation, there is no memory waste when the tree is not full.
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
